.TH SCROLLLOCK\-LED\-DAEMON 8 "2026-07-04" "1.0.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
scrolllock\-led\-daemon \- daemon that synchronizes a key press with the keyboard LED
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B scrolllock\-led\-daemon
[\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Scroll Lock LED Daemon listens for a key press and toggles the
corresponding keyboard LED. It runs as a background service managed
by systemd. When the keyboard is disconnected, it waits and
automatically reconnects.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-device \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Keyboard device path (e.g. /dev/input/event4).
Overrides auto\-detection.
.TP
.B \-\-led \fI\,PATH|NAME\/\fR
LED brightness file path or a name suffix such as
scrolllock, capslock, or numlock.
.TP
.B \-\-key \fI\,NAME\/\fR
Key to listen for (default: KEY_SCROLLLOCK).
.TP
.B \-\-set \fI\,on|off\/\fR
Set the LED state and exit (one\-shot mode).
.TP
.B \-\-toggle
Toggle the LED state and exit (one\-shot mode).
.TP
.B \-\-list
List available input devices and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-config \fI\,PATH\/\fR
Path to configuration file.
.TP
.B \-\-verbose
Enable debug logging.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help message and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/scrolllock\-led\-daemon.conf
System\-wide configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.config/scrolllock\-led\-daemon/scrolllock\-led\-daemon.conf
Per\-user configuration file.
.TP
.I /etc/systemd/system/scrolllock\-led\-daemon.service
systemd service unit.
.SH EXAMPLES
List available input devices:
.IP
scrolllock\-led\-daemon \-\-list
.PP
Run as a daemon (default):
.IP
scrolllock\-led\-daemon
.PP
Listen for F12 and control capslock LED:
.IP
scrolllock\-led\-daemon \-\-key KEY_F12 \-\-led capslock
.PP
Set LED on and exit:
.IP
scrolllock\-led\-daemon \-\-set on
.PP
Use a custom configuration file:
.IP
scrolllock\-led\-daemon \-\-config /etc/scrolllock\-led\-daemon.conf
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGTERM, SIGINT
Initiate a graceful shutdown.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.B 0
on success, or
.B 1
on failure.
.SH AUTHOR
Alan Santos
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR systemd (1),
.BR evdev (7)
